 resilient ways that queer people build social worlds using spaces and technologies in ways they were not intended.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Pornography. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438448794423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438448794/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles